class FloatWithUnits
{
    public $value;
    public $unit;

    public function __construct($value, $unit)
    {
        $this->value = $value;
        $this->unit = $unit;
    }

    public function show()
    {
        return "{$this->value} {$this->unit}";
    }
}
```
This method will take the `value` and `unit` fields of the struct and concatenate them with a space using the `{}` syntax. The resulting string will be in the format "1.8 meters".

Here's an example of how you could use this method:
```
$floatWithUnits = new FloatWithUnits(1.8, 'meters');
echo $floatWithUnits->show(); // Output: 1.8 meters
```
